A '''[[bay]]''' is an area of water bordered by land on three sides.

'''Bay''' may also refer to:
* [[Bay (horse)]], a color of the hair coats of some horses
* [[Bay leaf]], the aromatic leaves of several species of the Laurel family
* [[Bay Laurel]], the evergreen laurel tree species ''Laurus nobilis''
* [[Bay (architecture)]], a module in classical or Gothic architecture
* The name in English of a [[Ken (architecture)|ken]], a Japanese unit of measure and proportion
* [[Dog communication#Howls|Baying]], a kind of howl made by canines

;Places
* [[Bay, Haute-Saône]], a commune of France in the Haute-Saône department
* [[Bay, Laguna]], a municipality in the Philippines
** [[Bay River]], a river in this locality
* [[Bay, Somalia]]
* [[Bay, Arkansas]], USA
* Shorthand for various features, including
** [[San Francisco Bay Area]], or simply the Bay Area
** The [[Chesapeake Bay]] and other locally prominent bays
** [[Morecambe Bay]] - largest intertidal bay in England

;Radio
* [[102.1 Bay Radio]], a radio station in South Wales, originally launched as Swansea Bay Radio
* [[The Bay (radio station)]], in North West England
* [[The Bay 102.8]], a radio station in Dorset, England
* [[Bay Radio (Spain)]], a radio station serving the Valencian Community in Spain
* [[Bay Radio (Malta)]], a radio station located in Malta in Spain
* [[100.7 The Bay]], a classic rock radio station in Westminster, Maryland

;Transport
* [[Bay (TTC)]] subway station in Toronto
* BAY, the IATA airport code of [[Baia Mare Airport]] in Baia Mare, Romania
* [[Bay Station (OC Transpo)]], a bus stop in Ottawa's Central Transitway located downtown

;Miscellanea
* [[Chancellor Bay]], a royal scribe to an ancient Egyptian ruler
* [[Bay Trading Company]], a retailer of woman's clothes in the UK
* [[Sick bay]], nautical term for the location in a ship that is used for medical purposes
* Rose bay, a common name for ''[[Rhododendron maximum]]''
* [[Bay platform]], a dead-end platform at a railway station which has through lines
* [[The Bay School of San Francisco]] A private SF high school
* [[Drive bay]], the area for adding hardware in a computer
* [[The Bay]], a chain of department stores in Canada, subsidiary of the Hudson's Bay Company.
* [[Bay (surname)]]
* [[Bay Street (disambiguation)]]
* [[Bay Township (disambiguation)]]
