      <text xml:space="preserve">{{Infobox military conflict
|conflict=Battle of Bosworth Field
|partof=the [[Wars of the Roses]]
|image=[[File:Battle of Bosworth by Philip James de Loutherbourg.jpg|300px|alt=Battle scene with many figures. A knight atop a charger and wielding a lance unhorses another knight. Two unhorsed knights battle. Infantry advances from the right, led by a man with raised sword. Bodies litter the ground.]]
|caption=Battle of Bosworth Field, as depicted by [[Philip James de Loutherbourg]] (1740&amp;ndash;1812)
|date=22 August 1485
|place=Near [[Ambion Hill]], south of [[Market Bosworth]], England
|result=Decisive Lancastrian victory
|combatant1=[[File:Yorkshire rose.svg|15px|alt=White rose]] [[House of York]]
|combatant2=[[File:Lancashire rose.svg|15px|alt=Red rose]] [[House of Lancaster]]
|combatant3=[[File:Stanley.svg|15px|alt=White shield with diagonal blue stripe]] Stanley family
|commander1=[[Richard III of England]]{{KIA}} &lt;!-- highest ranking field commander only --&gt;
|commander2=[[Henry VII of England|Henry Tudor, Earl of Richmond]] &lt;!-- highest ranking field commander only --&gt;
|commander3=[[Thomas Stanley, 1st Earl of Derby|Thomas Stanley, 2nd Baron Stanley]] &lt;!-- highest ranking field commander only --&gt;
